<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Quake Rocks Indonesian Island  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   JAKARTA, Indonesia (AP) -- An earthquake with a magnitude of 5.4 jolted
Mataram, a town in central Indonesia, but there were no reports of damage or
casualties, seismologists said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
	   Musli, an officer of the Meteorology and Geophysics Agency, said the tremor
that struck Mataram on Lombok Island, was centered beneath the Indian Ocean, 33
miles southwest of Mataram. It had a depth of 60 miles below the sea floor.
</P>
<P>
	   ``The quake was felt in Mataram and surrounding areas as well as Denpasar,''
said Musli, who like many Indonesians uses one name.
</P>
<P>
	   Denpasar is the capital of Bali, Indonesia's foremost tourist destination.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
