<HEADLINE> Dow Gains 31l Nasdaq Is Up 4  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
    NEW YORK (AP) -- The Dow Jones industrial average is up 31 points in today's
early going. Advancing issues on the New York Stock Exchange hold a 7-6 lead
over decliners.
</P>
<P>
	   The Nasdaq Composite Index is ahead four points and the Standard &AMP; Poor's
500 Stock Index is up one point.
</P>
<P>
	   Wall Street will be watching for more earnings news, with Amazon.com
expected to post its results later today.
</P>
<P>
	   But by and large, the market is on interest rate watch.
</P>
<P>
	   The Federal Reserve will wrap up a two-day policy meeting in Washington.
</P>
<P>
	   The general consensus is that the central bank will announce a quarter-point
hike in short-term rates, after it concludes its meeting at about 2 p.m. EST.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
