<HEADLINE> Woman killed in shooting  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
    	   SYRACUSE, N.Y. (AP) -A man used a shotgun to kill his wife's friend
while the family's three children slept upstairs, police said.
<P>
	   Police said the killing appeared to have stemmed from a complicated domestic
dispute.
</P>
<P>
	   "The domestic situation involved these three people. Other than that I'm not
going to comment any further on how the relationship was set up," Sgt. Joseph F.
Sweeny said today.
</P>
<P>
	   When police arrived at the home and on the city's west side at 11:17 p.m.
Tuesday, they found Carol Lozott, 35, of Solvay dead from a fatal shotgun blast,
Sweeny said.
</P>
<P>
	   Two hours later, relatives of Ralph Kazmirski, 30, contacted police and
arranged for Kazmirski to surrender. He was charged with second-degree murder
and scheduled for arraignment today.
</P>
<P>
	   The shooting was witnessed by the estranged wife of Kazmirski, Jolan
Kazmirski. She told police her husband entered the home, got into an argument
and shot her friend Lozott at close range in the chest before fleeing in his
pickup truck.
</P>
<P>
	   Jolan Kazmirski's children - aged 6, 10 and 14 years - were upstairs at the
time of the shooting, but were not harmed. Ralph Kazmirski is the father of two
of the children. They did not see the killing, Sweeny said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
