<BODY>
<HEADLINE> New Buddy Holly Tune Performed  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
    MILWAUKEE (AP) -- A new tune created from lyrics Buddy Holly scribbled in a
notebook is being performed nearly 41 years after the rock and roll legend's
death in a plane crash.
</P>
<P>
	   Milwaukee drummer Victor DeLorenzo, formerly with the Violent Femmes, said
he first saw the notebook page in 1996, while visiting in New York with record
executive Howard Thompson, who had bought the page at auction.
</P>
<P>
	   On a later visit, DeLorenzo said he took a closer look at the writing and
decided it was Holly's attempt at lyrics to a song that was never completed.
</P>
<P>
	   Applying his own song-writing logic, he deciphered the repeated last line of
the chorus as "You get me in dutch."
</P>
<P>
	   "My whole idea was not to add anything," DeLorenzo said. When he got home to
his studio, he soon had the music for the lyrics written. "It was like my mind
was in possession of Mr. Holly for 10 minutes."
</P>
<P>
	   DeLorenzo planned to perform it this weekend but said he has no plans to
release a recording of the song.
</P>
</TEXT>
