<DATE_TIME> 2000-02-02 14:28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Two Pratt workers win $880,000 in age discrimination suit  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
    	   HARTFORD, Conn. (AP) - Two former Pratt &AMP; Whitney workers who claimed
they were laid off because of their ages have been awarded $880,000 in damages.
<P>
	   An eight-member jury in U.S. District Court in New Haven deliberated less
than 2 1/2 hours Tuesday before finding that the March 1997 layoffs by the jet
engine maker were discriminatory.
</P>
<P>
	   Robert Schanzer of West Hartford and Robert R. Madison of Longmeadow, Mass.,
filed the lawsuit in May 1998.
</P>
<P>
	   Both men were 53 years old and employees in Pratt's finance department when
they were notified that they were being laid off in an effort to reduce
operating costs.
</P>
<P>
	   The lawsuit claimed that most of those selected for layoff in the department
were older than 46. Although only 39 percent of department members were over 46,
all but one of the 33 workers laid off were over 46.
</P>
<P>
	   "It seemed a little more than coincidence that that many of the people they
laid off were above that age," juror Richard Barletta of Hamden said after the
six-day trial.
</P>
<P>
	   Gregg Adler, an attorney for Schanzer and Madison, told the jury that one of
the criteria Pratt used in evaluating employees before the layoff was "future
potential" - a criterion he said discriminated against older workers.
</P>
<P>
	   Pratt's lawyer, Albert Zakarian, conceded in his final argument that
Schanzer and Madison weren't bad employees. But he said the evaluation process
that preceded the layoff was designed to keep the better employees in the face
of cost-cutting needs dictated by competition.
</P>
<P>
	   "It's about honest people making tough decisions," he said.
</P>
<P>
	   The verdict included a total of $445,000 in damages for Schanzer and
$435,000 for Madison.
</P>
<P>
	   One other Pratt employee who was laid off in March 1997 has an
age-discrimination lawsuit pending in U.S. District Court in Hartford.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER> AP-ES-02-02-00 1428 </TRAILER>
