<HEADLINE> India Arms Smugglers Sentenced  </HEADLINE>
   By CHANDRA BANERJEE Associated Press Writer
<TEXT>
<P>
	   CALCUTTA, India (AP) -- A judge gave life sentences Wednesday to a British
arms dealer and five Latvians who parachuted crates of weapons intended for
revolutionaries into eastern India.
</P>
<P>
	   Peter Bleach, the arms trader, and the Latvian crewmen said they would
appeal their convictions to a higher court.
</P>
<P>
	   ``I am very disappointed, but not surprised,'' Bleach said outside the
courtroom.
</P>
<P>
	   The six were convicted of aiding insurgents who intended to wage war against
India, and procuring and bringing arms into the country five years ago.
</P>
<P>
	   The defendants also were fined $1,400. A seventh defendant, an Indian, was
acquitted for lack of evidence. All five Latvian men were members of Latvia's
large ethnic-Russian minority. Latvia and Russia said they would push for
leniency.
</P>
<P>
	   The case was closely watched because it touched on the international arms
market and involved some of the most serious charges brought against Western
defendants.
</P>
<P>
	   The six have spent four years in jail since they were arrested for dropping
the arms from a cargo plane onto a field in the eastern Indian state of West
Bengal.
</P>
<P>
	   The prosecution claimed the assault rifles, rocket launchers, grenades and
missiles were intended for the Ananda Marg, a fanatical anti-communist Hindu
religious group in West Bengal, a state with a communist government.
</P>
<P>
	   Judge P.K. Biswas said: ``The convicts do not deserve any leniency. It was a
clear case that security and safety of the nation was at stake.''
</P>
<P>
	   Bleach argued that he had secretly kept the British intelligence services
informed of the plan to fly arms to India.
</P>
<P>
	   Although they reportedly acknowledge receiving Bleach's tip-off, the British
services say they warned the arms dealer not to get involved. The Ananda Marg
have denied it was the intended recipient of the weapons.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER> AP-NY-02-02-00 1621 </TRAILER>
