<HEADLINE> Boy Falls Nine Stories, Breaks Leg  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   TBILISI, Georgia (AP) -- A 13-year-old boy who fell nine stories from the
roof of a building survived with only a broken leg, national television reported
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
	   The boy, Lasha Gogichaishvili, was playing with friends on the roof of the
building when he tripped and fell over the edge, the report said. On his way
down, he plunged through three clotheslines stretched between apartment
buildings, which partially broke his fall.
</P>
<P>
	   Doctors in the Black Sea city of Batumi, where the boy lives, said he
suffered no damage to internal organs and that he could return home Thursday.
</P>
