<HEADLINE> El Salvador Bans Movie 'Stigmata'  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
    SAN SALVADOR, El Salvador (AP) -- Facing pressure from conservative groups,
Salvadoran authorities on Wednesday banned the U.S. film "Stigmata."
</P>
<P>
	   The 1999 film depicts a young woman suffering puncture wounds through the
wrist, like those in Christ's crucifixion, and questions the teachings of the
Catholic church.
</P>
<P>
	   Morena Serpas, director of the office of Public Performances in this
predominantly Catholic country, said the film has been withdrawn "because it is
an attack on public order." He said members of Catholic groups and conservative
art associations had requested the move.
</P>
<P>
	   The film stars Patricia Arquette and Gabriel Byrne. It opened in San
Salvador, the capital, last week and had earned $40,000.
</P>
</TEXT>
