<HEADLINE> Suns 114, Clippers 68  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
    PHOENIX (AP) -- Clifford Robinson bounced back from his All-Star snub to
score a game-high 21 points as the Phoenix Suns beat the Los Angeles Clippers
114-68 Wednesday night for the most lopsided win in nearly 11 years.
</P>
<P>
	   The Suns' 46-point margin of victory matched the second-largest in franchise
history and the largest since they beat Sacramento 140-85 on April 17, 1989
after having beaten San Antonio 137-91 two days earlier.
</P>
<P>
	   The Clippers have lost 11 straight road games and 16 of their last 18
overall. Los Angeles was without starting forward Lamar Odom, who did not dress
because of flu-like symptoms.
</P>
<P>
	   Robinson, who was not picked as an All-Star reserve Tuesday despite a
team-best 20.0-point scoring average, was 8-for-15 from the floor over the first
three quarters. Luc Longley was the only Suns starter to play in the fourth
quarter.
</P>
<P>
	   Tom Gugliotta scored 14 points, and Jason Kidd, Anfernee Hardaway and Randy
Livingston had 12 each for the Suns, who have won nine straight against the
Clippers.
</P>
<P>
	   Tyrone Nesby scored 17 and Eric Piatkowski added 10 for the Clippers, who
are 3-21 on the road.
</P>
<P>
	   Nesby converted a three-point play with 3:07 left in the first quarter to
pull Los Angeles within 19-17. But the Suns outscored the Clippers 25-5 over the
next 10:03 en route to a 58-32 halftime lead.
</P>
<P>
	   The Clippers missed their first six shots in the second quarter and were
held scoreless until Piatkowski's 3-pointer with 6:29 left in the period.
</P>
<P>
	   Kidd kept the Suns rolling in the second half, scoring four of Phoenix's
first six points as the Suns opened a 64-34 lead with 9:38 left in the third
quarter.
</P>
</TEXT>
