<DATE_TIME> 2000-02-02 23:50 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Stolen Car Found With Baby Inside  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   BRIGHTON, Mich. (AP) -- A minivan with a 10-month-old baby girl inside was
stolen and abandoned outside a restaurant about 25 miles away, police said
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
	   The child was in the back seat of a Chrysler minivan taken from outside
Marv's Meats and Bakery in Brighton about 1 p.m. Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
	   A suspect was arrested in Pontiac and was to be formally charged Thursday,
state police said late Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
	   Police said the girl's mother had run into the store and when she came out,
the van was gone.
</P>
<P>
	   About two hours later, the owner at Joe's Country Restaurant in Pontiac
called police after his wife heard a baby crying in a car in the parking lot.
Pontiac is about 25 miles northeast of Brighton.
</P>
<P>
	   The baby appeared fine and the mother was on her way to pick her up.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
